label: ABCD Equivalence
rdfs_comment: Used to show the xpath(s) to the equivalent term(s) in the current version of the Access to Biological Collections Data (ABCD) schema.

label: Organized in Class
rdfs_comment: Used to organize properties within classes for easier human understanding.
dcterms_description: Does not imply domain or range membership in the class.

label: Decision
rdfs_comment: Used to reference the formal decision that resulted in this version of the term.

label: Status
rdfs_comment: Used to indicate if the term is recommended for use or if it is only of historical significance.
dcterms_description: Values for this term should be either "recommended" or "historical".

label: Vocabulary
dcterms_description: See the TDWG Standards Documentation Standard (http://www.tdwg.org/standards/147) for usage guidelines.

label: Term List
rdfs_comment: An IRI-identified set of terms that is part of a vocabulary and that includes terms within the vocabulary that are grouped in a particular way, such as falling within a particular namespace.
dcterms_description: See the TDWG Standards Documentation Standard (http://www.tdwg.org/standards/147) for usage guidelines.

label: Layer
rdfs_comment: Used to indicate the centrality of vocabulary terms.
dcterms_description: Used in Audubon Core (http://www.tdwg.org/standards/638). "1" indicates central terms likely to be meaningful in most instances. "2" includes terms useful for describing particular kinds of instances, or instances with highly detailed descriptions.

label: Required
rdfs_comment: Indicates that a term is required to conform to a profile.
dcterms_description: Used in Audubon Core (http://www.tdwg.org/standards/638). "Yes" indicates that the term must be included to be a conformant Audubon Core record. "No" includes that a term is optional in a conformant Audubon Core record.

label: Repeatable
rdfs_comment: Indicates that the term may be repeated in a metadata record.
dcterms_description: Used in Audubon Core (http://www.tdwg.org/standards/638). "Yes" indicates that a term may be repeated in a conformant Audubon Core record. "No" indicates that a term must not be repeated in a conformant Audubon Core record.
